File: plugins/slack/src/slack-api.ts, lines 397-401.

Current code:
```
if (response.status === 429) {
  const retryAfterStr = response.headers.get('Retry-After') ?? 'unknown';
  const retryMs = retryAfterStr ? parseInt(retryAfterStr, 10) * 1000 : 60000;
  throw ToolError.rateLimited(`Slack API rate limited (429). Retry after ${retryAfterStr} seconds.`, retryMs);
}
```

Bug: When Retry-After header is absent, retryAfterStr = 'unknown'. Since 'unknown' is truthy, parseInt('unknown', 10) returns NaN, so retryMs = NaN.

Fix: Get the raw header value (which is null when absent). Parse it as a number only if present. Guard against NaN. Pass undefined when no valid retry delay can be determined. Adjust the error message to not include 'unknown'.

Example fix:
```
if (response.status === 429) {
  const retryAfterRaw = response.headers.get('Retry-After');
  const retrySeconds = retryAfterRaw !== null ? parseInt(retryAfterRaw, 10) : NaN;
  const retryMs = Number.isNaN(retrySeconds) ? undefined : retrySeconds * 1000;
  const msg = retryMs !== undefined
    ? `Slack API rate limited (429). Retry after ${String(retrySeconds)} seconds.`
    : 'Slack API rate limited (429).';
  throw ToolError.rateLimited(msg, retryMs);
}
```
